sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K624031
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pYMB indicates pUC19 with ori+Pmsp1+rep. In this construct, YN-13-R and YC-CHAMP are ligated in the downstream of ori+Pmsp1+rep, aimed at serving as optogenetic wireless neurostimulator with OFF state (no BRET between EYFP and rLuc) as default mode. BiFC between YN and YC is anticipated in the default state as well.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shang-Jui Tsai
